With the first sequencer (Genome Analyzer) it was possible to sequence 1 gigabase (Gb) of data in a single run. Nowadays, the output reaches 6000 Gb when using NovaSeq6000. The technology allows advantages and drawbacks too. It provides the lowest per base cost, huge amount of data, better performance along homopolymeric regions, and low error rate. The read length limitation (maximum 2×150 bp or 2×300 bp) remains an unsolved problem [
 Ari and Arikan, 2016; 
 Heather and Chain, 2016; 
 Kulski, 2016; 
 Liu et al., 2012; 
 Mardis, 2013; <
 https://www.illumina.com/systems/sequencing-platforms.html> (accessed: 2018.09.22)].
